title: Too Few Risk Takers.
author-name: Black, J.
author-name: de Meza, D.
abstract:This paper shows that costly state verification creates a bias against risky activities in the policy relevant sense that everyone may gain if entry to them is subsidised. The result holds even in the presence of private insurance. In fact, it may be preferable to ban private insurance and rely on subsidies to risky occupations.
