title: A Note on Discontinuous Value Functions and Strategies in Affine-Quadratic Differential Games.
author-name: Jensen, H.
author-name: Lockwood, B.
abstract: We present an economic example of an affine-quadratic differential game where in Markov-perfect Nash equilibrium, the value function of a player is discontinuous in the model's parameters, implying that the strategy of that player is also discontinuous, even though the data of the game (state equation and pay-offs) are continuous in the parameters. Sufficient conditions ruling out such discontinuities are presented for the general scalar case.
