title: Policy Regime Changes and the Long-Run Sustainability of Fiscal Policy: An Application to Greece.
author-name: Makrydakis, S.
author-name: Tzavalis, E.
author-name: Balfoussias, A.
abstract: This paper questions the widespead practice of assessing the hypothesis of long-run fiscal policy sustainability by means of conventional unit-root tests that do not allow for the possible impact of regime shifts. Using the Greek economy as a model case, the Zivot- Andrews squential integrability testing procedure which allows for the endogenous determination of possible regime changes is deployed to this end.
