title: Specific and Ad Valorem Tariffs Are Not Equivalent in Trade Wars.
author-name: Lockwood, B.
author-name: Wong, K.Y.
abstract: This note argues that when two countries choose optimal tariffs in a trade war, specific tariffs are not equivalent to ad valorem tariffs even if all markets are competitive. In particular, it shows that if a country's trading partener switches a specific tariff to an an valorem tariff that yields the same revenue at the initial trade point, the former country has an incentive to lower its tariffs.
