title: Posted vs. Negotiated Prices under Incompelte Information.
author-name: Natale, P.
abstract: This paper addresses the issue of selecting pricing institutions in a bilateral monopoly. Suppose a bayer and seller can benefit from exchanging one unit of a good. The selelr is entitled to select the pricing institution. He can either make a take-it-leave-it offer or enter a bargaining game.
