title: European Monetary Union, Asymmetric Shocks and Inertia
author-name: Driver, Rebecca 
author-name: Wren-Lewis, Simon 
abstract: This paper assesses the scale of the costs of European Monetary Union when shocks are asymmetric. This is done considering time consistent policies within a small theoretical two country model, with parameter values chosen from empirical work. The model builds on earlier work by incoporating a forward looking inflation mechanism. Our results suggest that there are significant costs associated with Monetary Union, particularly when fiscal policy is not used as a stabilisation tool.
keywords: European Monetary Union, Asymmetric shocks, Inertia
